1) Log De‑Duplication + Diagnostics Control

Goal
- Show only one instance of each error/warning, record the first ID that caused it, suppress repeats for other IDs.
- Make this behavior a toggle in the diagnostics module.

Implementation Notes
A) Logger changes (src/lib/utils/logger.ts)
- Add a “dedup mode” that can be enabled via localStorage config.
- Track a per‑session in‑memory map:
  - Key: {tag}:{level}:{message}:{contextKey}
  - Value: {firstId, firstTimestamp, count}
- Define contextKey rules:
  - For token‑specific logs, use token id as “firstId” but do NOT include id in the key unless we want per‑token logging.
  - Desired behavior here: same message across ids should collapse to 1 log → key should exclude id.
- On repeated logs, increment count and suppress output.
- Optional: emit a periodic summary log every N minutes (e.g., “Suppressed 182 repeats of X”).

B) Diagnostics toggle (src/screens/AdminDiagnosticsScreen.tsx)
- Add a new section “Log de‑duplication” with:
  - Toggle (on/off)
  - Optional mode: “per‑message” vs “per‑message+source tag”
  - Optional: “reset dedup state” button (clears in‑memory map)
- Store settings in localStorage (e.g., LOG_DEDUP_ENABLED, LOG_DEDUP_MODE).

C) Where to apply
- All log output: token preview warnings, chunk read warnings, CORS / fetch failures.
- Ensure error logging still happens once so issues are visible.

Ease / Safety
- Ease: Medium (small code change but touches global logger).
- Safety: High (does not change behavior of data loading, only logging).
- Risk: Low (log suppression only).

