2) BNS (.btc) Name Resolution for Addresses

Goal
- If an address has a BNS name, show the name in UI (primary), with address as secondary.
- When searching/lookup, accept either address or .btc name.

Implementation Notes
A) Resolver module
- Add a small resolver module: src/lib/bns/resolve.ts
- Functions:
  - resolveNameToAddress(name: string) => address | null
  - resolveAddressToName(address: string) => name | null
- IMPORTANT: Confirm the authoritative API / endpoint in Stacks BNS docs (Hiro/Stacks). Do not hard‑code until verified.

B) Caching strategy
- In‑memory cache + persistent cache (IndexedDB or localStorage).
- TTL recommended (e.g., 24h) + negative caching for missing names (short TTL, e.g., 1h).
- Avoid per‑card lookups during initial grid render; resolve names on demand or in background batches.

C) UI integration points
- Viewer / Wallet owner displays: show “name (address)” when resolved.
- Wallet lookup input: if .btc provided, resolve to address before lookup.
- Ensure accessibility: include full address in title/tooltip.

D) Concurrency + rate limiting
- Use the same read‑only request limiter or a dedicated small queue.
- Batch requests if API supports it; otherwise debounce and cache aggressively.

Ease / Safety
- Ease: Medium (new network calls + caching + UI formatting).
- Safety: Medium (requires careful API validation + rate‑limit handling).
- Risk: Moderate if API endpoints change; mitigate by isolating resolver and using robust caching.

