3) External Marketplace / Indexer Support Document

Goal
- Provide a clear, technical guide for marketplaces to reconstruct Xtrata inscriptions from chunks.
- Ensure third parties can render Xtrata NFTs consistently (e.g., Gamma.io).

Implementation Notes (Document Outline)
A) Contract Read‑Only Functions (per contract version)
- get-last-token-id
- get-inscription-meta (owner, creator, mime‑type, total‑size, total‑chunks, final‑hash, sealed)
- get-token-uri
- get-chunk / get-chunk-batch
- get-svg / get-svg-data-uri
- get-dependencies

B) Reconstruction Algorithm
1. Call get-inscription-meta(tokenId)
2. Compute expected chunk count (from meta.total-chunks; if missing, estimate from first chunk size)
3. Fetch chunk 0 first to determine chunk size
4. Use get-chunk-batch when supported; otherwise fetch sequential chunks
5. Join chunks in order; trim to total-size
6. Validate final-hash (if provided)
7. Derive mime type from meta; sniff bytes if needed
8. Render based on mime:
   - image/svg+xml => use svg data or bytes
   - audio/video => stream or lazy load
   - text/html => render in sandboxed iframe
   - text/.. => text preview + download

C) Token URI usage
- Token URI can point to off‑chain metadata or image.
- Use as fallback; on‑chain bytes should be canonical.

D) Dependencies / recursive inscriptions
- Use get-dependencies(tokenId), resolve each dependency the same way, then render the outer HTML with recursive bridge if needed.

E) Caching recommendations
- Cache chunks, assembled bytes, and thumbnails (LRU + TTL)
- Use cache‑first behavior to avoid repeated reads

F) Network / API details
- Document chain endpoints used for read‑only calls
- Provide guidance for rate‑limit handling and retries

Doc Location Proposal
- Add to docs/: docs/marketplace-integration.md
- Reference contract versions in docs/contract-inventory.md

Ease / Safety
- Ease: High (documentation only, no app changes).
- Safety: High (no runtime impact). Accuracy depends on contract docs; ensure review against contract sources.

